What did I miss?: The following are my go to places: Xian Noodles (crazy good noodles and made from scratch), Paco's Tacos (an excellent, hearty breakfast taco and similar to what I grew up having in South Texas), Sap's (hands down the best green curry), Chago's Caribbean (something different), Casa Colombia, Blue Dahlia (frittatas and NiÃ§oise salad), Contigo (free ox tongue slider on Wednesday), Whip In, and Che Zee (decent and often overlooked). Dai Due is new, and their supper club menu has been delicious.   I also noticed the following are good and popular, but not on your list: Mandola's (not the best Italian, but good for Austin...), Gourdough's, Frank, Peche, Foreign and Domestic, Hillside Farmacy, Amy's, and Noble Sandwich.
